Chinese and Saudi curators join hands to hold the first Saudi contemporary art biennial - Xinhua Xinhua News Agency, Riyadh, Dec. 12 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia's first contemporary art biennial, the Diriyah Contemporary Art Biennial, was officially opened to the public on Dec. 11 at the JAX Art Zone in Diriyah, located in the northwest of the Saudi capital Riyadh. A total of 64 artists from Saudi Arabia, China and other places participated in the exhibition. The Biennale is jointly curated by the Saudi Diriyah Biennale Foundation and the Ullens Center for Contemporary Art (UCCA) in China, with Tian Feiyu, director of UCCA, as artistic director. According to the curatorial team, the theme of the Biennale is "Crossing the River by Touching the Stones", which is a metaphor for the reform strategy adopted during the period of social and economic transition, and reflects the current situation of social and cultural development in Saudi Arabia. The Biennale covers an area of nearly 12,000 square meters, with exhibition halls spanning six interconnected buildings, and is presented in six units: "Crossing the River by Touching the Stone," "Heritage as Experiment," "Thinking on the Edge," "Toward the Public," "Beautiful New World," and "On the Spirit of Art. Among them, the works of 27 Saudi artists account for more than 40% of the total number of exhibits, including painting, installation art and performance art, etc. The works of 12 Chinese artists are also of great interest, some of them using recycled materials in novel ways, such as Xu Bing's "The Story Behind Series - Endless Pictures of Streams and Mountains" (2014), in which he reconstructs a classic In "Behind the Story Series: Endless Streams and Mountains" (2014), Xu Bing reconstructed a classic landscape painting from waste. Barkley, CEO of the Diriyah Biennale Foundation, said he hoped the Biennale would create an international dialogue and give a global audience the opportunity to learn about Saudi Arabia's thriving cultural industries and creative community and to strengthen interaction. Tian Feiyu said: "The goal of the Biennale is twofold, both to engage Saudi contemporary art in a global dialogue and to integrate Saudi audiences into the world of contemporary art . "It is understood that a series of lectures will be held during the opening week of the Biennale, in which artists, curators and opinion leaders from the creative industry will discuss topics such as cross-cultural exchange and the development of contemporary art.
